Column Comment.0: UNIQUE WELL IDENTIFIER: A unique name, code or number designated as theprimary key for this row.
Column Comment.1: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.2: PRESSURE OBSERVATION NUMBER: A sequence number uniquely identifying theproduction test being performed in the well.
Column Comment.3: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.4: ASSIGNED FIELD: The reported field assigned to the well for the well perforation.
Column Comment.5: BASE DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the base of the pressure testinterval.
Column Comment.6: BASE DEPTH OUOM: Base measured depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.7: STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.
Column Comment.8: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.9: EVENT OBSERVATION NUMBER: Unique identifier for this observation
Column Comment.10: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.11: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.12: FLOW CASING PRESSURE: The flowing pressure measured in the casing. This isthe pressure measured between the casing and tubing at the wellhead when fluidsare flowing.
Column Comment.13: FLOWING CASING PRESSURE OUOM: Flowing casing pressure original unit ofmeasure.
Column Comment.14: FLOW TUBING PRESSURE: The flowing pressure measured in the tubing. This isthe pressure on the fluid in the tubing at the wellhead as the fluids are flowing.
Column Comment.15: FLOWING TUBING PRESSURE OUOM: Flowing tubing pressure original unit ofmeasure.
Column Comment.16: INITIAL RESERVOIR PRESSURE: The initial reservoir pressure. (The pressure onfluid in a subsurface formation)
Column Comment.17: INITIAL RESERVOIR PRESSURE OUOM: Initial reservoir pressure original unit ofmeasure.
Column Comment.18: POOL DATUM REFERENCE: The reference for POOL DATUM DEPTH, such as sealevel.
Column Comment.19: POOL DATUM DEPTH: The depth at pool datum. The datum is defined inWELL_PRESSURE.POOL_DATUM.
Column Comment.20: POOL DATUM DEPTH OUOM: Pool datum depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.21: POOL: Unique identifier for the pool into which the completion that is tested is made.
Column Comment.22: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.23: STRING IDENTIFIER: Number or code uniquely identifying a production string withina well.
Column Comment.24: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.25: WELL STRING FORMATION OBSERVATION NUMBER: A sequential observationnumber used to uniquely identify each completed (perforated) formation (layer) that iscontributing production to a well string.
Column Comment.26: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.27: SHUTIN CASING PRESSURE: The shutin pressure measured in the casing.Pressure measured between the casing and the at the wellhead when the well isshutin.
Column Comment.28: SHUTIN CASING PRESSURE OUOM: Shutin casing pressure original unit ofmeasure.
Column Comment.29: SHUTIN TUBING PRESSURE: Value for the shutin pressure measured in the tubing(or at the wellhead when the well is shutin).
Column Comment.30: SHUTIN TUBING PRESSURE OUOM: Shutin tubing pressure original unit ofmeasure.
Column Comment.31: STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the stratigraphic name set. Astratigraphic name set is an unordered collection of stratigraphic units, that may be inuse for a Lexicon, a geographic area, a project, a company etc.
Column Comment.32: TOP DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the top of the pressure testinterval.
Column Comment.33: TOP DEPTH OUOM: Top measured depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.34: STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: unique identifier for the stratigraphic unit.
Column Comment.35: WELL DATUM DEPTH: The depth at well datum. The WELL datum is defined inWELL.DATUM_DEPTH.
Column Comment.36: WELL DATUM OUOM: Well datum depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.37: TEST_NUMBER: A number used to uniquely identify the individual test occurringwithin a test run or trip.
Column Comment.38: RUN NUMBER: A number which uniquely identifies the run or trip into the well for thepurpose of operating a test
Column Comment.39: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.40: WELL TEST TYPE: identifies the general type of test used to evaluate the potentialof the well. For example, Drill St em Tests (DST), Repeat Formation Tests (RFT),Initial Potential(IP).
Column Comment.41: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.42: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.43: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.44: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.45: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.46: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.47: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
